{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Select · Stisla{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Select</h1>
    <p class="lead">A styled trigger with a custom popup for picking one or more values.</p>
    <p>Reach for Select when you want the look of <a class="link" href="/native-select">Native select</a> but a popup you can style. It supports type-to-jump like a native field and shows a single-line summary in multi mode. For typing-ahead search, see <a class="link" href="/combobox">Combobox</a>. For a free-form input that suggests options, see <a class="link" href="/autocomplete">Autocomplete</a>.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-stisla-select</code> to a <code>&lt;select class="select"&gt;</code> to hydrate. The original element stays in the DOM (hidden) so form submission works as authored.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="basicSelect" class="field__label">Country</label>
      <select class="select" id="basicSelect" name="country" data-stisla-select data-placeholder="Pick one">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="id">Indonesia</option>
        <option value="my">Malaysia</option>
        <option value="sg">Singapore</option>
        <option value="ph">Philippines</option>
        <option value="th">Thailand</option>
        <option value="vn">Vietnam</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Keyboard</h2>
    <p>The trigger behaves like a native <code>&lt;select&gt;</code>.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><kbd>Space</kbd>, <kbd>Enter</kbd>, <kbd>ArrowDown</kbd>: open</li>
      <li><kbd>ArrowUp</kbd> / <kbd>ArrowDown</kbd>: move highlight (looping)</li>
      <li><kbd>Home</kbd> / <kbd>End</kbd>: first / last enabled option</li>
      <li><kbd>Enter</kbd> / <kbd>Space</kbd>: select the highlighted option (toggles in multi)</li>
      <li><kbd>Escape</kbd>: close</li>
      <li><kbd>Tab</kbd>: close and move to the next focusable element</li>
      <li>Type a letter: jump to the first option that starts with it (extend the buffer by typing more letters within 500ms)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Multiple</h2>
    <p>Add the <code>multiple</code> attribute to let users pick several values. The trigger renders the first chosen label plus <code>+N more</code> when there's overflow, so the field stays on one line. Click an already-selected option in the popup to toggle it off.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="multiSelect" class="field__label">Tags</label>
      <select class="select" id="multiSelect" name="tags" multiple data-stisla-select data-placeholder="Add tags">
        <option value="bug">Bug</option>
        <option value="docs" selected>Docs</option>
        <option value="feat" selected>Feature</option>
        <option value="qa">QA</option>
        <option value="perf">Performance</option>
        <option value="a11y">Accessibility</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sizes</h2>
    <p>Three sizes match the input scale. Add <code>.select--compact</code> or <code>.select--roomy</code> to the <code>&lt;select&gt;</code>; the trigger button inherits the variant.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="demo-stack" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <select class="select select--compact" data-stisla-select data-placeholder="Small" aria-label="Small select">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="1">One</option>
        <option value="2">Two</option>
        <option value="3">Three</option>
      </select>
      <select class="select" data-stisla-select data-placeholder="Default" aria-label="Default select">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="1">One</option>
        <option value="2">Two</option>
        <option value="3">Three</option>
      </select>
      <select class="select select--roomy" data-stisla-select data-placeholder="Large" aria-label="Large select">
        <option value=""></option>
        <option value="1">One</option>
        <option value="2">Two</option>
        <option value="3">Three</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Option groups</h2>
    <p>Wrap related options in <code>&lt;optgroup&gt;</code> to label sections inside the popup.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="groupedSelect" class="field__label">City</label>
      <select class="select" id="groupedSelect" data-stisla-select data-placeholder="Pick a city">
        <option value=""></option>
        <optgroup label="Indonesia">
          <option value="jkt">Jakarta</option>
          <option value="bdg">Bandung</option>
          <option value="sby">Surabaya</option>
        </optgroup>
        <optgroup label="Malaysia">
          <option value="kul">Kuala Lumpur</option>
          <option value="pen">Penang</option>
        </optgroup>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Disabled</h2>
    <p>Add <code>disabled</code> to block interaction and dim the field. The trigger inherits <code>:disabled</code> and the popup won't open.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="disabledSelect" class="field__label">Plan</label>
      <select class="select" id="disabledSelect" data-stisla-select disabled>
        <option value="free" selected>Free</option>
        <option value="pro">Pro</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Browser validation</h2>
    <p>Native HTML constraints work because the source <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> stays in the DOM. Add <code>required</code> with a placeholder <code>&lt;option value=""&gt;</code> and the form blocks submit until the user picks a real value. The browser's tooltip is suppressed because it would anchor to the hidden source, so render the error text with <code>.field__error</code>. The trigger picks up <code>aria-invalid</code> automatically when constraints fail and clears it once the new value is valid.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <form class="demo-stack" style="max-width: 24rem;" onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); alert('submitted');">
      <div class="field">
        <label for="reqSelect" class="field__label">Plan</label>
        <select class="select" id="reqSelect" name="plan" required data-stisla-select data-placeholder="Pick a plan">
          <option value=""></option>
          <option value="free">Free</option>
          <option value="pro">Pro</option>
          <option value="team">Team</option>
        </select>
        <div class="field__description">Hit Submit without picking. The trigger paints invalid and takes focus. Pick any option and the red clears on its own.</div>
      </div>
      <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary">Submit</button>
    </form>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Server validation</h2>
    <p>Set <code>aria-invalid="true"</code> on the source <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> and the trigger picks it up. Clearing it works in reverse, so your form library can keep treating the source as the form field.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="invalidSelect" class="field__label">Plan</label>
      <select class="select" id="invalidSelect" data-stisla-select aria-invalid="true" aria-describedby="invalidSelectError">
        <option value="free">Free</option>
        <option value="pro">Pro</option>
        <option value="team">Team</option>
      </select>
      <div id="invalidSelectError" class="field__error">This plan isn't available in your region.</div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Events</h2>
    <p>Listen for <code>stisla:select:change</code> to react to selection changes. The event's <code>detail.value</code> is a string for single, an array for multi. The underlying <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> also fires its own native <code>change</code> event, so existing form code keeps working.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="field" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="eventSelect" class="field__label">Theme</label>
      <select class="select" id="eventSelect" data-stisla-select>
        <option value="light" selected>Light</option>
        <option value="dark">Dark</option>
        <option value="auto">Auto</option>
      </select>
      <div id="eventSelectOut" class="field__description">Current: light</div>
    </div>
    <script>
      (function () {
        var el = document.getElementById('eventSelect');
        var out = document.getElementById('eventSelectOut');
        el.addEventListener('stisla:select:change', function (e) {
          out.textContent = 'Current: ' + e.detail.value;
        });
      })();
    </script>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>The trigger reuses the <code>--select-*</code> variables from <a class="link" href="/native-select">Native select</a>. The popup adds its own <code>--select-*</code> variables that follow the same surface recipe as <a class="link" href="/menu">Menu</a>, Combobox, and Autocomplete.</p>
    <p>On touch devices (<code>@media (pointer: coarse)</code>) <code>--select-font-size</code> is bumped to <code>1rem</code> so iOS Safari doesn't zoom the viewport on focus. The browser auto-zooms any field with computed font-size below 16px and never zooms back; desktop keeps the tighter default.</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Variable</th><th>Use</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>--select-height</code></td><td>Trigger height (matches <code>.input</code>)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-padding-inline</code></td><td>Trigger horizontal padding</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-radius</code></td><td>Corner radius, shared by trigger and popup; the compact and roomy variants reassign it on the trigger</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-indicator</code></td><td>Chevron SVG; data: URL with literal stroke per theme</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-bg</code></td><td>Surface, shared by trigger and popup</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-border-color</code></td><td>Border color, shared by trigger and popup</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-shadow</code></td><td>Popup shadow</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-item-padding-block</code> / <code>--select-item-padding-inline</code></td><td>Option row padding</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-item-min-height</code></td><td>Option row min height</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-item-bg-hover</code></td><td>Highlighted row background (mouse hover + keyboard nav)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--select-item-bg-active</code></td><td>Currently-selected row background</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Because the popup variables are shared, setting <code>--select-radius</code> at <code>:root</code> retunes every popup the same way. Set it on <code>.select__popup</code> for a one-off.</p>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
